rvice (TikTok), but getting content tailored to you. And let me tell you, i=
t is incredibly engrossing, even if it is, for now, a roguelike experience =
to get to the good stuff.

Microsoft, as noted by the Skype launch, is not running from Bing chat, alt=
hough the company has certainly been doing its darnedest to stuff Sydney in=
 a box; Snap, meanwhile, included this disclaimer in its blog post:

As with all AI-powered chatbots, My AI is prone to hallucination and can be=
 tricked into saying just about anything. Please be aware of its many defic=
iencies and sorry in advance! All conversations with My AI will be stored a=
nd may be reviewed to improve the product experience. Please do not share a=
ny secrets with My AI and do not rely on it for advice.

While My AI is designed to avoid biased, incorrect, harmful, or misleading =
information, mistakes may occur. Please press and hold on any message from =
My AI to submit feedback. We look forward to hearing about your experience =
with My AI.

That doesn=E2=80=99t sound like =E2=80=9CSydney unleashed=E2=80=9D, but the=
n again, you do get to give My AI its own name, and Snap is an entertainmen=
t/social app. Moreover, Snap has a lot less to lose than Microsoft, and thu=
s more incentives to make My AI more interesting than not. In short, the pr=
oduct, context, and incentives all seem more aligned to make this the most =
interesting chat bot yet.

The other piece that is interesting is that Snap also has the right busines=
s model in place, i.e. a subscription. Inference is still very expensive, a=
nd a subscription will cover those costs, even as My AI becomes a reason to=
 subscribe. Yes, Snap claims they want to make My AI broadly available, but=
 I suspect that is a function of costs over which Snap doesn=E2=80=99t have=
 much direct control, and besides, having a real reason to subscribe and, t=
o the extent My AI is a compelling companion, not churn, has an outside cha=
nce to be impactful on Snap=E2=80=99s business. It=E2=80=99s certainly wort=
h a shot, and I look forward to trying it out.

